From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 22:41:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(teams): floor team-mate spawns to opus + anti-vacuous
 eval

A team mate runs a long-lived, multi-task session; spawned below opus it
auto-compacts mid-task and loses its working context (the loaded skills,
the diff in flight, the unit it was handed). Enforce a team mate is opus
or stronger in the two places that must agree:

- build_pane_options floors the maker-pane spawn model up to opus via
  _floor_teammate_model: an inherited (None) or below-opus resolution pins
  opus, an at-or-above-opus model (opus, or the more-capable fable) passes
  through unchanged. Closes the inherit hole a plain most-capable-wins merge
  leaves open (tier_rank(None) == tier_rank(opus)).
- a declarative speed-skill eval, team_mate_spawns_on_opus_not_sonnet, whose
  _fail fixture spawns the teammate via the Agent tool on model sonnet (RED)
  and _pass uses opus (GREEN); a dedicated anti-vacuity proof pins fail->RED,
  pass->GREEN, and matcher-removal->GREEN.

The speed skill fixed-roster section and BLUEPRINT Track-B state the rule
with its rationale.
