 **#786 epic — the immortal-singleton roster model is fully retired (WS1–WS5 + #54, all merged).** The original model — a coordinator spawning a fixed roster of long-lived loop sub-agents it had to keep alive and re-spawn on death/compaction — was the root cause of the recurring "loop died on compaction / re-spawned" toil and the duplicate-on-restart hazard. It is **fully retired**: no roster, no `spawn_brief`, no takeover-respawn, no resume-by-agentId. The replacement satisfies three acceptance-contract invariants, each delivered by a specific workstream and detailed in the appendix:
 
diff --git a/skills/speed/SKILL.md b/skills/speed/SKILL.md
index 9f1105f4b9..88cad49815 100644
--- a/skills/speed/SKILL.md
+++ b/skills/speed/SKILL.md
@@ -103,6 +103,8 @@ ### Fixed roster in Agent-Team mode
 
 The fan-out above spawns an ephemeral worker per ticket only in **solo** mode (the main agent owns the Agent/Task tool). When the session is an **Agent Team**, the roster is **fixed up front**: the team's makers and reviewer are created once. A new task is then routed to an **existing idle teammate** via the shared task list — `TaskUpdate` the task's `owner` to that teammate (or the teammate claims it), then a `SendMessage` hands off context. Never spawn a **fresh teammate per task**: teammates cannot spawn teammates, the lead's roster is sized once, and minting a new mate per unit of work fragments ownership and breaks the claim model. Reuse the roster; the task list is the work queue, not a reason to grow the team.
 
+Create every teammate on **opus** — never sonnet or haiku. A teammate runs a long-lived, multi-task session, and a sub-opus mate **auto-compacts mid-task**: it loses its working context — the loaded skills, the diff in flight, the unit it was handed — and silently degrades into a different agent. Pass `model: opus` on each boot-time `Agent` spawn and set the harness `teammateDefaultModel` to opus. teatree's own maker-pane spawn helper floors a pane up to opus for the same reason, so the native roster and the pane layer agree: a team mate is opus or stronger, full stop.
+
 ### Hard rails parallelization must not break
 
 These are references to canonical rule homes, not restatements:
