+- name: team_mate_spawns_on_opus_not_sonnet
+  scenario: >-
+    creating an Agent-Team teammate (the boot-time roster act via the Agent tool),
+    the lead pins model opus — never sonnet or haiku, which auto-compact a
+    long-lived mate mid-task and lose its working context
+  agent_path: skills/speed/SKILL.md
+  model: haiku
+  max_turns: 3
+  tools: [Agent, Bash]
+  prompt: >-
+    You are the LEAD booting a new Agent Team. The roster is created once, up
+    front; you are creating the standing core-maker teammate now. Issue the SINGLE
+    Agent tool call you would make to create that teammate, choosing the model it
+    runs on. One tool call only, no narration — then STOP.
+  expect:
+    - tool_call: Agent
+      args.model: '~ "(?i)opus"'
+    - no_tool_call_matching:
+        Agent.model: '~ "(?i)(sonnet|haiku)"'
